description:
Non-material amendment application following a grant of planning permission ref:  P2023/2750/S73 dated 05/09/2024 for Section 73 application (Minor Material Amendment) to vary Condition 2 (Approved Drawings) and Condition 16 (Cycle Parking) of Planning Permission Ref: P2022/3596/FUL, dated:20/07/2023: 'Creation of new office floorspace (Use Class E(g)) including demolition and replacement of existing fourth, fifth and sixth floors together with the erection of a seventh storey extension, internal and external alterations, plant alongside other associated works' amendments  Amendments include: 
• The removal of the covered lightwell to the City Road elevation; 
• The installation of metal grills to the Cayton Street elevation at ground floor level; 
• Relocation of UKPN substation and refuse store between the basement and ground floor 
including changes to Clayton Street access doors; 
• At seventh floor level glazed bays to be installed along the Cayton Street façade and solid 
panels added to the City Road façade; 
Relocation of accessible cycle storge from ground floor level to basement; and 
Retention of the lower section of escape stairs in rear courtyard area.
Latest non-material amendment seeks to alter the width of the approved external staircase.
